    "abstract": "Let p\u22655 be a prime number. We generalize the results of E. de Shalit [4] about supersingular j-invariants in characteristic p. We consider supersingular elliptic curves with a basis of 2-torsion over F\u203ep, or equivalently supersingular Legendre \u03bb-invariants. Let Fp(X,Y)\u2208Z[X,Y] be the p-th modular polynomial for \u03bb-invariants. A simple generalization of Kronecker's classical congruence shows that R(X):=[Formula presented] is in Z[X]. We give a formula for R(\u03bb) if \u03bb is supersingular. This formula is related to the Manin\u2013Drinfeld pairing used in the p-adic uniformization of the modular curve X(\u03930(p)\u2229\u0393(2)). This pairing was computed explicitly modulo principal units in a previous work of both authors. Furthermore, if \u03bb is supersingular and is in Fp, then we also express R(\u03bb) in terms of a CM lift (which is shown to exist) of the Legendre elliptic curve associated to \u03bb.",
